#T_SP=webanno.custom.Referent|entity|infstat
#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=DS : How does it feel to be looked-up to by the kids , by America 's future ?
#Text=AN :
#Text=[ Laughs ]
#Text=It 's terrifying ! [ Laughs ]
#Text=DS : Do you see parents at the show ?
#Text=AN :
#Text=Oh , yeah , oh yeah .
#Text=Parents with their kids —
#Text=DS : That must reduce the crotch grabbing .
#Text=AN :
#Text=[ Laughs ]
#Text=Yeah , a little bit of macho posturing .
#Text=I tell you man , it 's a really big thrill , just to go out and play in towns we 've never been to .
#Text=Kids come out and they know all the songs .
#Text=We 've had situations where we 've played New York and girls are in the front row singing along to our guitar solos .
#Text=Like , wow ... we 're on stage playing and we can hear them singing back at us .
#Text=Something else Bryn and I have noticed is at larger festival shows when we get to the end of our shows we play Push Push Lady Lightning , the kids would just light up and start air guitaring !
#Text=But not actually playing air guitar , but playing air guitar hero -- like , they knew where all the notes were !
#Text=DS : Which is a lot different for audiences of many bands .
#Text=AN :

#Text=Absolutely ! I ca n't imagine other bands having the same experience , because we come from such a unique perspective that a large part of our music is driven by the instrumentals , and that sort of thing .
#Text=DS : Your fans are so engaged with your music , far more than most bands have .
#Text=Most bands they have fans who feel their music speaks to them , but your fans can say , ' I learned to play guitar on your shit and not on Eleanor Rigby ! '
#Text=AN :
#Text=It 's an honor .
#Text=It 's still unbelievable to me .
#Text=I had a message from a friend of mine who was at Guitar Center and he heard one of the kids cranking out one of our songs when he was trying out the guitar .
#Text=To me , it 's like we made it .
#Text=DS : At this point of your career , you 're not playing stadiums , but you 're also not playing Otto 's Tiki Lounge on a Tuesday night .
#Text=When you reflect upon it , what do you think about ?
#Text=AN :
#Text=In the past two years , since Bryn and I started this project , we 've both been playing in bands locally in Boston for years .
#Text=We had some mixed success , we played large venues in and around Boston .
#Text=We got to the point where we said fuck it , we just want to have some fun and we 'd laugh a lot going over old Ozzy Osbourne stuff we listened to as kids , just giggle about it .
#Text=Bang Camaro started that way , something for us to do and invite our friends to come sing on it .
#Text=Now , just two years later , it 's amazing what happens when you stop trying .
#Text=It 's something not contrived or born of any desire to reach an audience .
#Text=We just did it for fun , and that spoke to people more than anything else we worked on .
